13. Imaginarium Use

For the Path of Re-Rendering, The Serpent Power is the subtle-body cartography source.

Ordinary consciousness appears as a flat ego-world: body here, world there, mind inside, objects outside. Avalon’s tantric map breaks that flatness. The body becomes a layered cosmos. Speech becomes mantra. Sound becomes structure. Desire becomes Śakti. Attention becomes ascent. The spine becomes a world-axis.

Core Imaginarium thesis:

The human being is a rendered mandala. The cakras are not merely psychological symbols but imaginal interfaces where body, sound, element, deity, and consciousness meet. Kuṇḍalinī is the hidden power by which the rendered world can be traced back to its source.

