3. Structural Map
A. Devī’s Question

Devī asks what Bhairava truly is beyond forms, mantras, ritual categories, and doctrinal appearances.

B. Bhairava’s Reply

Bhairava redirects the question from theology to direct entry into awareness.

C. The 112 Dhāraṇās

A sequence of contemplative gateways using breath, sound, space, fear, wonder, desire, perception, void, dream, sleep, body, sky, light, and inner stillness.

D. Nondual Recognition

The practices are not ends in themselves; they are doors into Bhairava-consciousness.

E. Closing Frame

The multiplicity of methods resolves into a single principle: awareness recognizes itself through any experience when grasping relaxes.

