Prāṇāyāma refines the body-breath field and produces inner lightness.

F. Pratyakṣa — Direct Perception

Dhyāna opens inner seeing and meditative perception.

G. Nirliptatā — Non-attachment

Samādhi culminates the process in freedom and non-clinging.

