5. Coverage Clusters
Cluster A — Mind as Rendering Field

The world is experienced through vṛttis: modifications, waves, formations, and movements of citta.

Cluster B — Nirodha

Yoga is the stopping, restraining, or settling of these formations so the seer can abide in its own nature.

Cluster C — Affliction Machinery

Ignorance, egoity, attachment, aversion, and clinging to life structure the self-world.

Cluster D — Eight-Limbed Reordering

Ethics, posture, breath, withdrawal, concentration, meditation, and samādhi form one continuous re-rendering ladder.

Cluster E — Saṃyama and Deep Cognition

Concentration becomes an instrument for penetrating structures of experience.

Cluster F — Powers as Distraction

Extraordinary capacities are acknowledged but subordinated to liberation.

Cluster G — Kaivalya

The final aim is not energetic ascent or deity-identification, but radical freedom of the seer.

